{
  "stem": "10699.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they took us to the station.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there they put us in these trucks, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was June, you mustn't forget.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A hundred, a hundred, a hundred people in a trucks, you know, more.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no room to-- there was no room to, to, to, to, to stretch your legs or do anything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were no-- the conditions-- there were babies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were old people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there, in that-- in that convoy-- and they were already with us at the time in the-- in the-- in the barracks-- but we didn't know them-- was a family Dreyfus, a mother, father, and two girls, who lived in-- near Strasbourg before the war and were arrested in [FRENCH], not in St-Etienne-- outside.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "French Jews for the last 300, 400 years-- they were with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It is the, the girls-- the-- one-- only one survived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is the girl who, after the war, married my brother.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was all the time with me after that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we were, like, together in the same, same wagon in the same conditions.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was hot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was smelly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was no water, no food, no nothing-- a few belongings, I don't know what.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my mother only felt sorry for her children that they should be here in, in that wagon in these conditions and god knows what.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Even my dress was torn from the-- from being so squashed together and hot and sweaty.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And you-- and, and no room to move.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So when I got up, somehow, my dress was torn, you know, from sitting like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "When we arrived after three days in Birkenau, we must have arrived-- it was early morning, dawn, 5:00 or 6:00.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
